AUDIO: 'What if your AI coding assistant got a little bit smarter every single day on its own while you sleep? Not because a new model dropped, because the system you built around it learns from every mistake it makes, writes that lesson down, and never repeats it.'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'Most people use Claude Code like a goldfish. Brilliant for one session, and then it forgets everything. And tomorrow, you re-explain your entire project from scratch. In the next few minutes, I\'m going to'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'show you how to flip that. How to turn Claude Code into a self-improving system that compounds. I call it the REPS framework, because just like reps in the gym, every single loop'

[00:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'makes it stronger. Steel the whole thing. Let\'s build it. Here\'s the core idea, and it\'s the part almost everyone misses. A static prompt is a tool. A loop is a system.'

[00:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'The difference between them is compounding. If Claude gets 1% better every day, and actually remembers it, then in a year, it\'s not 1% better. It\'s 37 times better. That\'s a flywheel. And every flywheel'

[01:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'needs four gears, which is exactly what REPS stands for. R, record. Give Claude a memory it can write to itself. E, evaluate. Let it grade its own work, so it knows'

